title: For Sale/Trade:  .303 Enfield 1918 Collectable
postcontent:
A great rifle from the Great War. This collectable, but very shootable, .303 No. 1 Mk III* British WWI Enfield is dated 1918 and was made by Standard Small Arms (SSA) in the UK. It was part of the "peddle scheme," where a Birmingham company contracted out for parts made throughout Great Britian and would assemble them at its factory. It worked, but not as well as hoped, making this a collectable Enfield, as well as a very good shooter. Rifle is in great shape, very good bore, no rust, no pitting, good bluing, wood was de,greased, oiled and waxed. Holding this is holding history: made for the war to end all wars and then used again in WWII. (To anyone who responded to a "trade rifle for pistol" ad previously placed, a computer crash flushed away all emails. Sorry. But here it is again.) 

Asking $325.00; WA Driver's license necessary; and would prefer CPL. Will need bill of sale for my records. Would use in trade for 9 mm S&W 3913 or Sig P6.
